{
  "stem": "13817.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The interesting part, which I didn't know at that time, is when I came back after the war to Germany, one priest had saved one Torah.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He had grabbed it and took it away without knowing-- anybody knowing it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "When he gave it back to me after I came back, that was the first Torah we had in Cologne to start over the Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But then they burned the Torahs, the other ones.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They burned everything in that place.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Not the building itself because there were caretakers living in there which was not Jewish.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So-- but the other things they made a big bonfire in front of the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And then the mob started going from business to business, from house to house where Jews lived.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] went through some places like-- like a tornado hit the house.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The businesses were-- were damaged and all torn apart, looted.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We were lucky.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I don't know why or what.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "In our house, only one show window was broken and the door was-- was [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] damaged with an axe.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "That was all what happened to us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But my grandma and my aunt-- to-- old lady in her 60s with her unmarried daughter lived in a house where they grew up with-- with, let's see, three-- five children.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "A big house.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And the mob went through that house like a tornado hit the whole house.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "There wasn't one thing in-- in this house-- damaged--",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
